<subSubSection id="C37A6519712AFFF4D9940A61FE3400B9" pageId="3" pageNumber="488" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="8BDF3692712AFFF4D9940A61FB9E00F9" blockId="3.[174,1233,1295,1513]" pageId="3" pageNumber="488">
Diagnosis. The species is characterized by the complete occipital carina; strongly swollen basally dark brown clypeus; fore wing with vein 3 
<emphasis id="B914EA80712AFFF4DA140A5EFC280019" box="[867,921,1328,1353]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="488">rs-m</emphasis>
present; propodeum with strong lateromedian longitudinal carinae reaching well defined area apicalis; orange hind femora; granulate metasomal tergites 1–2; strongly upcurved female ovipositor, about as long as the hind tibia length; and widened tyloids on male flagellomeres 3–6.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BDF3692712AFFF4D9940ADEFE3400B9" blockId="3.[174,1233,1295,1513]" pageId="3" pageNumber="488">
D i s t r i b u t i o n. Western Palaearctic; 
<collectingCountry id="F3777602712AFFF4DBD40AC1FCB70099" box="[675,774,1455,1481]" name="Ukraine" pageId="3" pageNumber="488">Ukraine</collectingCountry>
: 
<collectingRegion id="49A4F870712AFFF4DA640AC1FC7F0099" box="[787,974,1455,1481]" country="Ukraine" name="Kharkiv" pageId="3" pageNumber="488">Kharkiv Region</collectingRegion>
(
